0},{"title":"Author/Chew Leng Lim","target":"Author/Chew Leng Lim","line":101},{"title":"Author/Sharafuddin Khairuddin","target":"Author/Sharafuddin Khairuddin","line":102},{"title":"Author/Thomas Lufkin","target":"Author/Thomas Lufkin","line":103},{"title":"Author/Sharafuddin Khairuddin","target":"Author/Sharafuddin Khairuddin","line":104},{"title":"Author/Thomas Lufkin","target":"Author/Thomas Lufkin","line":105},{"title":"Author/Valerie Chun Ling Lin","target":"Author/Valerie Chun Ling Lin","line":106},{"title":"Author/Valerie C.-L. Lin","target":"Author/Valerie C.-L. Lin","line":107},{"title":"Author/Valerie Chun Ling Lin","target":"Author/Valerie Chun Ling Lin","line":108},{"title":"PDF","target":"biblib/lim_tetratricopeptide_2016/lim_tetratricopeptide_2016.pdf","line":110}],"metadata":{"id":"lim_tetratricopeptide_2016","type":"article-journal","title":"Tetratricopeptide repeat domain 9A modulates anxiety-like behavior in female mice.","issued":{"date-parts":[[2016]]},"DOI":"10.1038/srep37568","container-title":"Scientific Reports","abstract":"Tetratricopeptide repeat domain 9A (TTC9A) expression is abundantly expressed in the brain. Previous studies in TTC9A knockout (TTC9A−/−) mice have indicated that TTC9A negatively regulates the action of estrogen. In this study we investigated the role of TTC9A on anxiety-like behavior through its functional interaction with estrogen using the TTC9A−/− mice model. A battery of tests on anxiety-related behaviors was conducted. Our results demonstrated that TTC9A−/− mice exhibited an increase in anxiety-like behaviors compared to the wild type TTC9A+/+ mice. This difference was abolished after ovariectomy, and administration of 17-β-estradiol benzoate (EB) restored this escalated anxiety-like behavior in TTC9A−/− mice. Since serotonin is well-known to be the key neuromodulator involved in anxiety behaviors, the mRNA levels of tryptophan hydroxylase (TPH) 1, TPH2 (both are involved in serotonin synthesis), and serotonin transporter (5-HTT) were measured in the ventromedial prefrontal cortex (vmPFC) and dorsal raphe nucleus (DRN). Interestingly, the heightened anxiety in TTC9A−/− mice under EB influence is consistent with a greater induction of TPH 2, and 5-HTT by EB in DRN that play key roles in emotion regulation. In conclusion, our data indicate that TTC9A modulates the anxiety-related behaviors through modulation of estrogen action on the serotonergic system in the DRN.","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Lim","given":"Lee Wei","literal":""},{"family":"Lim","given":"Lee Wei","literal":""},{"family":"Shrestha","given":"Smeeta","literal":""},{"family":"Or","given":"Yu Zuan","literal":""},{"family":"Shrestha","given":"Smeeta","literal":""},{"family":"Shrestha","given":"Smeeta","literal":""},{"family":"Or","given":"Yu Zuan","literal":""},{"family":"Tan","given":"Shawn Zheng Kai","literal":""},{"family":"Tan","given":"Shawn","literal":""},{"family":"Chung","given":"Hwa Hwa","literal":""},{"family":"Chung","given":"Hwa Hwa","literal":""},{"family":"Sun","given":"Yang","literal":""},{"family":"Sun","given":"Yang","literal":""},{"family":"Lim","given":"Chew Leng","literal":""},{"family":"Lim","given":"Chew Leng","literal":""},{"family":"Khairuddin","given":"Sharafuddin","literal":""},{"family":"Lufkin","given":"Thomas","literal":""},{"family":"Khairuddin","given":"Sharafuddin","literal":""},{"family":"Lufkin","given":"Thomas","literal":""},{"family":"Lin","given":"Valerie Chun Ling","literal":""},{"family":"Lin","given":"Valerie C.-L.","literal":""},{"family":"Lin","given":"Valerie Chun Ling","literal":""}],"citation-key":"lim_tetratricopeptide_2016","year":"2016","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["Tetratricopeptide repeat domain 9A modulates anxiety-like behavior in female mice."],"author-links":["[[Author/Lee Wei Lim]]","[[Author/Lee Wei Lim]]","[[Author/Smeeta Shrestha]]","[[Author/Yu Zuan Or]]","[[Author/Smeeta Shrestha]]","[[Author/Smeeta Shrestha]]","[[Author/Yu Zuan Or]]","[[Author/Shawn Zheng Kai Tan]]","[[Author/Shawn Tan]]","[[Author/Hwa Hwa Chung]]","[[Author/Hwa Hwa Chung]]","[[Author/Yang Sun]]","[[Author/Yang Sun]]","[[Author/Chew Leng Lim]]","[[Author/Chew Leng Lim]]","[[Author/Sharafuddin Khairuddin]]","[[Author/Thomas Lufkin]]","[[Author/Sharafuddin Khairuddin]]","[[Author/Thomas Lufkin]]","[[Author/Valerie Chun Ling Lin]]","[[Author/Valerie C.-L. Lin]]","[[Author/Valerie Chun Ling Lin]]"],"attachment":["[[biblib/lim_tetratricopeptide_2016/lim_tetratricopeptide_2016.pdf|PDF]]"],"related":[[]]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[],"last_embed":{"hash":"njljkc","at":1774951890751}},"smart_blocks:Research/@lim_tetratricopeptide_2016.md#---frontmatter---": {"path":null,"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.01874298,-0.01397248,-0.00428858,-0.00785738,-0.02147315,0.06939986,0.0708809,0.04254421,0.0115475,-0.03880244,0.00122609,-0.05000373,0.02264976,0.01613102,0.00172636,0.05709567,-0.00674766,0.02039228,-0.04153089,0.01303671,0.0207206,-0.03848409,0.05175008,-0.01270149,0.03854995,0.01272833,-0.08925123,-0.02102089,-0.04360686,-0.219497,0.01649524,-0.02428317,0.00306354,0.01149068,-0.01624884,-0.01192595,-0.08690012,0.0175091,-0.04465469,0.06950389,0.02138649,0.01192956,-0.03844871,-0.06452596,0.00885397,-0.02986397,0.00232665,-0.00113893,-0.00548888,-0.03185759,0.03573016,-0.03402125,0.00287263,0.06454007,0.00082571,0.0498988,0.03298638,0.07170182,0.04013612,0.03022741,0.04682086,0.05081011,-0.17778562,0.06996471,0.08641628,0.0109101,-0.08472737,0.01704756,0.04407661,0.06916954,-0.05015259,0.05934521,0.01100023,0.02592332,0.05309535,-0.01407981,0.00951551,-0.04802193,0.03392551,-0.02270471,0.03970725,0.05050077,0.05543168,-0.03730696,0.00079606,-0.09235355,-0.01863406,-0.06499715,-0.00608561,0.00379382,-0.03708585,-0.0790704,0.02770727,-0.02211222,-0.03366656,-0.00738872,0.01775716,-0.0082229,-0.03478041,0.10783706,0.00094542,0.04465483,-0.07352401,0.03451529,0.01928243,